LIX. No plant however is so renowned among the Hiera boe< Romans as hiera botane (“ sacred plant ''). Some call it asistereon, and Latin writers verbenaca. This is the plant which I mentioned as carried to the enemy by envoys.a With this the table of Jupiter is swept,⁰ and homes are cleansed and purified. There are two kinds of it 3 one has many leaves and is thought to be female, the other, the male, has fewer leaves. Each kind has several sprigs that are slender, a cubit long and angular; the leaves are smaller and narrower than those of the oak3 the indentations 100 316 deeper, the blossom is grey, and the root long and slender. It grows everywhere in flat, moist localities. Some authorities do not distinguish these two kinds but make of them one only, since both have the same properties.
